\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Course Introduction and Logistics\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 Welcome!\
This course is designed to equip you with the core tech stack of the future: Large Language Models (LLMs), Context Engineering (Prompt Engineering, Data Engineering and Retrieval Augmented Generation), Fine-Tuning, Tool Use and Agents. These are all techniques to build on top of LLMs and customize them to specific applications. They boil down to ensuring the LLMs have clear and effective instructions (Prompting), can find and use the most relevant data for the task (Data Collection, Curation and RAG), are adapted towards specific tasks (Fine-tuning), and are connected together in more complex pipelines with access to external tools (Workflows and Agents).\
Some of our students that completed this certification and mastered these skills have transitioned into AI focussed careers finding roles with titles such as \'93AI Engineer\'94 or \'93LLM Developer\'94. Others choose to bring these powerful new capabilities into their existing roles, projects or start-ups.\
