\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Course Overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 We approach LLM development as a modular process. You start by building a functional Python-based Proof of Concept (PoC), perhaps even with a simple python based front-end, targeting achievable "quick wins" for a specific niche task. From there, using evaluation frameworks and feedback, you iteratively enhance components of the pipeline\'97swapping models, adding advanced techniques, refining data sources, improving prompts\'97to progress towards a Minimum Viable Product (MVP). This iterative method is adaptable, suitable for anything from personal projects to enterprise tools. We'll guide you through this entire cycle.\
The course structure reflects this practical approach. Part 1 comprises 60 code-intensive lessons guiding you through the AI Tutor project, covering everything from data handling and basic RAG to advanced techniques and deployment. Part 2 expands your toolkit with additional models, tools, and frameworks which you may find useful in your own LLM projects. Part 3 shifts focus to strategy, helping you identify promising project ideas, understand product defensibility, and consider the economic landscape of Generative AI. Part 4 is dedicated to your final project submission.\
Purchasing our course gets you lifetime access and it is a continuously evolving curriculum. Updated every month with new tools, methods, and case studies, the course will stay relevant as the field changes. You won\'92t need to buy new courses every time new techniques come out!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 LLM Building Blocks\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec0 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
