\cf0 \strokec2 \
Modular and iterative development of an LLM pipeline. Many techniques can be used and stacked together in different combinations when building an LLM pipeline. Source: Towards AI\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Often the best LLM products will be built with a combination of a wide range of models and tools from different providers. We remain impartial regarding specific tools and models, discussing various options and teaching you how to choose the best for your current task. While lessons will demonstrate specific models (like OpenAI's GPT-5, Google's Gemini 2.5 Pro and Flash, Anthropic's Claude, META's Llama family) and frameworks (primarily LlamaIndex, with exposure to LangChain), the principles learned are transferable. Many components can be swapped in your own projects. This course aims to take you beyond initial experimentation, showing you how to overcome LLM limitations and build production-ready applications. We hope it empowers you to create valuable tools, advance your career, or launch new ventures in the AI space.\
A quick note on theory: our focus is intensely practical. We cover only the theoretical underpinnings necessary to understand 
\f4\i how
\f2\i0  to effectively adapt and use LLMs, not the deep mathematics or ML theory required for training models from scratch. We'll provide enough context to grasp the 'why' behind the techniques, enabling you to build robust applications.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Who Should Take This Course?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 This course caters to a broad audience, from those new to AI to experienced engineers and data scientists transitioning into LLM development.\
Prior knowledge of coding and basic Python is a prerequisite. However, Python is known for its simple and intuitive syntax, so it is generally quick to pick up for a confident developer (particularly if you use LLM tools to help explain and teach python concepts as you go!). Therefore, Python can also be self-taught in parallel with this course.\
If you have no prior knowledge of computer science, then we recommend first taking our course, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://academy.towardsai.net/courses/python-for-genai"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Python Primer for Generative AI}}
\f1\b  (also available in a bundle offer)
\f2\b0 . This python course is also valuable for experienced software developers without python knowledge - but if this is you we recommend skipping past explanations of computer science fundamentals)!\
Conversely, 
\f1\b deep AI or mathematics knowledge is 
\f5\i not
\f1\i0  required.
\f2\b0  The beauty of working with prebuilt foundation LLMs is that they handle much of the complexity. Our goal is to teach you how to leverage these pre-existing capabilities effectively, not how to build them from the ground up. We'll give you the necessary first-principles understanding of how LLMs operate to build better applications, without getting lost in unnecessary theoretical depth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Learning Resources\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 To help you with your learning process, we are sharing our open-source {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aitutor.towardsai.net/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 AI Tutor chatbot}} to assist you when needed. This tool has been created using the same tools we teach in this course. We build a RAG system that provides an LLM with access to the latest documentation from all significant tools, such as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.langchain.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 LangChain}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.llamaindex.ai/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 LlamaIndex}}, including our previous courses.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

